issue.body:
Is there an easier way to handle errors? The best I can see is to manually safely check the status:
```ts
const [ queryState ] = useRequest(queryConfig);
if(queryState?.status && queryState?.status >= 400) {
    alert('error')
}
```

It would be nice if a boolean was provided: 
```ts
const [ queryState ] = useRequest(queryConfig);
if(queryState.failed) {
    alert('error')
}
```

The definition of `failed` could default to >=400 or provide a custom callback in the config (similar to axios [validateStatus](https://axios-http.com/docs/handling_errors)). Is there a better option I'm not seeing that's already available?

